observations.recommendation:
We recommended that the Local Chief Executive:
a. Require the Municipal Accountant to send within ten (10) days before the
expiration of the prescribed period a written reminder under signature of the LCE or
his duly authorized representative enjoining officials and employees concerned to
settle their cash advance;
b. Direct the Municipal Accountant not to sign claims for additional cash advance until the
previous cash advance is settled;
c. Compel the Municipal Accountant to cause the immediate withholding of salaries and
claims of officers and employees who failed to settle their cash advances within the
prescribed period after being sent notice and demand;
